gate[say:indra]:#Indu, flow on with pleasant stream, to the _#Devas.

gate[say:indra]:Pour hitherward, as _#Indra Self, _#Indu, that gladdening stream of thine.

gate[say:indra]:Flow to the filter hitherward, pouring that ancient gladdening juice, Streaming forth _#power and high _#renown.

gate[say:indra]:Hither the sparkling drops have flowed, like waters down a steep descent, they have reached _#Indra purified.

gate[say:indra]:Whom, having passed the filter, While he disports him in the wood.

gate[say:indra]:The juice pour forth, for offering and service of the _#Devas, to him who bears away the draught.

gate[say:indra]:Effused flows onward with his stream to _#Indra, to the _#Deva, so that his will may strengthen him.

gate[say:indra]:Soul of the _#offering, the juice effused flows quickly on, he keeps his ancient wisdom of a _#Sage.

gate[say:indra]:So pouring forth, as _#Indra _#Friend, best _#Gladdener! For the banquet, even in secret, he storest _#hymns.

